  "texts": [
    "Finally, in (§5) I introduce an Anscombean alternative, based on a non-standard reading of a key action theoretic claim about the identity and constitution of intentional actions, the so-called Anscombe-Davidson principle.",
    "This alternative resolves the objections canvased in (§4), giving HEC's supporters reasons to adopt it (and their opponents 1 3 (2025) 205:47 reason to stick with the Davidsonian account).",
    "While positive reasons to embrace HEC must be sought elsewhere, this paper seeks to redraw some dividing lines in the contemporary debate.",
    "Since its introduction, HEC has been promoted as a transformative outlook on cognition, but too few of its supporters have considered how far it might entail a corresponding shakeup in the received picture of human agency.",
    "To have a mind is to be a special sort of information processing system."
  ]
}